United States--Spokane River Valley (Idaho and Wash.)

Label on verso: DATE: June 27, 1941; OP 65-2-93-146,  Dist. 1; PHOTO BY: Morgan Fitz, Camp Kettle; COUNTY: Stevens; Neg. No. 914; TITLE: Columbia River Reservoir Clearing Project; CAPTION: SPOKANE RIVER VALLEY (About May 15th) LOOKING SOUTH; The Spokane River, swelling with lake water as the Spokane river combines with Columbia river backwater behind Grand Coulee dame, is seen in this view looking south below the Detillion bridge which is seen in the middle distance. The Detillion bridge is now removed and the roads seen leading to it have been abandoned. Clearing line as the ultimate height of the reservoir lake is seen on either side of the valley. US WPA 729

[Grand Coulee Dam 345]
